{
  "id": "RAW_c82e42ac",
  "title": "a16z「25 本书」清单：这 10 本，帮创始人完成 80% 的认知升级",
  "url": "https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==&mid=2247511665&idx=1&sn=b016e74fafeff0a41ee024eb6be637c0",
  "date": "2025-11-26 07:31:00",
  "author": "硅谷科技评论",
  "siteName": "硅谷科技评论",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0.578px;text-wrap: wrap;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;\">\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;\">\n     <div mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0.578px;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;\">\n      <div mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"margin-top: 20px;margin-bottom: 20px;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;letter-spacing: 2px;\">\n       <div data-width=\"100%\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;width: 677px;vertical-align: bottom;border-radius: 8px;border-style: dashed;border-width: 2px;border-color: rgb(0, 145, 212);box-shadow: rgba(0, 145, 212, 0.22) 3.53553px 3.53553px 0px;\">\n        <div mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"letter-spacing: 0.578px;text-wrap: wrap;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;\">\n         <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\" data-pm-slice=\"3 2 [&quot;para&quot;,{&quot;tagName&quot;:&quot;section&quot;,&quot;attributes&quot;:{&quot;mpa-from-tpl&quot;:&quot;t&quot;,&quot;style&quot;:&quot;letter-spacing: 0.578px;text-wrap: wrap;-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;&quot;},&quot;namespaceURI&quot;:&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;}]\">\n          <p data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\" style=\"margin-left: 8px;margin-right: 8px;\"><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">\"If you want to beat experts as an outsider, you can just read 25 books.\"</span></span></strong></p>\n          <p style=\"margin-left: 8px;margin-right: 8px;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这是 a16z 在与</span></span><em><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Khosla Ventures</span></span></strong></em><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;投资人Keith Rabois 对谈时抛出的观点，也成为了他们新栏目&nbsp;</span></span><em><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">You can just read 25 books</span></span></em><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;的缘起。为了落地这句话，a16z 找来了自家创始人和合伙人，整理了一份真正塑造过他们世界观的 25 本书单。</span></span></p>\n          <p style=\"margin-left: 8px;margin-right: 8px;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">但对身处一线的创业者和投资人来说，一个更现实的问题是：在时间极度稀缺的前提下，这 25 本里，先读哪几本，才能最快「升级系统」？</span></span></p>\n          <p style=\"text-align: center;\" nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028003\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"0.6397984886649875\" data-s=\"300,640\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"794\" type=\"block\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=af4f2803&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdPdPJttqemzb9sE1jlpWyOH7wNcDRuwMeVfqwFBo6G5VMdAMHyicicNHA%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n         </div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n     <p class=\"mp_profile_iframe_wrp\" nodeleaf=\"\"><mp-common-profile class=\"custom_select_card mp_profile_iframe\" data-pluginname=\"mpprofile\" data-nickname=\"硅谷科技评论\" data-alias=\"svtr01\" data-from=\"0\" data-headimg=\"http://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_png/CHwGFH7ibtQYOkcfd0t8GBFFYmyMiaAtKB1TYb3O0f5HKwrCkSgXeuSrPMmDV0ia7CQ5siaTg9lxqlaNXwCDfXKFDA/0?wx_fmt=png\" data-signature=\"全球前沿科技，创业投资孵化\" data-id=\"MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==\" data-service_type=\"1\"></mp-common-profile></p>\n    </div>\n    <p data-pm-slice=\"0 0 []\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这是SVTR丨硅谷科技评论连续三年向大家推荐书单，从</span><a class=\"normal_text_link\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\" href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==&amp;mid=2247502029&amp;idx=1&amp;sn=6054f097e6f2ac7fc98c1dd8eaa65f9f&amp;token=1183514688&amp;lang=zh_CN&amp;scene=21#wechat_redirect\" textvalue=\"\" linktype=\"text\" data-linktype=\"2\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">硅谷的读书人：OpenAI CEO 的阅读清单</span></a><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，到</span><a class=\"normal_text_link\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\" href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==&amp;mid=2247508130&amp;idx=1&amp;sn=dedd2dba2e22cfe186c20e0aa38d1124&amp;token=1183514688&amp;lang=zh_CN&amp;scene=21#wechat_redirect\" textvalue=\"\" linktype=\"text\" data-linktype=\"2\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">2024 年必读人工智能书单：如何使用和理解该技术？</span></a><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">再到</span><a class=\"normal_text_link\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\" href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==&amp;mid=2247509584&amp;idx=1&amp;sn=0e399cf5ab4698ff606c204b14925aec&amp;token=1183514688&amp;lang=zh_CN&amp;scene=21#wechat_redirect\" textvalue=\"\" linktype=\"text\" data-linktype=\"2\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">真正能穿越周期的人，读透这9本全球顶级创投书单</span></a><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">。我们认为读书是提升认知的最好方式之一。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">结合 a16z 原文及 SVTR 长期在 AI 创投圈的观察，我们从原书单中精选了&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">「创始人 &amp; 投资人必读 Top 10」</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，并按四个核心维度重新构建了阅读路径：</span></span></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">商业本质</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">：从「县城小店」到「伟大公司」</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">产品变现</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">：定价、创新与颠覆</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">组织管理</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">：招聘决策与 CEO 的时间</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">心力建设</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">：风险认知、周期与意义</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\"></p>\n   <h3 style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 24px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">一、从「县城小店」到「伟大公司」：生意到底怎么做？</span></span></h3>\n   <p></p>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">1.《Sam Walton: Made in America》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028005\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.6371077762619373\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"733\" data-width=\"733\" data-height=\"1200\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=6b5642aa&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdCSIpqnibibrkr4sXkdaM2nzmxTiaDJBZND8s5dbEDicmZIbcGZF8UQxPnw%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">中文名：《山姆·沃尔顿自传：美国制造》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Sam Walton（山姆·沃尔顿）</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，沃尔玛（Walmart）和山姆会员店（Sam’s Club）创始人，曾多次被《福布斯》评为全美首富，是现代连锁零售业最具影响力的企业家之一。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">John Huey</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，资深商业记者，曾任《时代》集团（Time Inc.）总编辑，长期报道全球商业领袖，是本书的共同作者与整理者。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人： Qasar Younis ，Applied Intuition 联合创始人/CEO</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">很多人把沃尔玛视为一个精密的「庞大零售系统」，但山姆·沃尔顿讲述的，是一个非常「土」的故事：</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">在美国「县城」开小店，从选址、压成本，到把员工变成合伙人；一点点把「天天平价」「农村包围城市」刻入组织本能；用几十年时间，把几条朴素的原则滚雪球般变成全球帝国。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;这是一本关于「怎么做生意」的底层教材。在中国和硅谷，我们见过太多「一上来就想做平台、做生态」的 BP。沃尔顿告诉你：</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">先把一间店做好，再谈生态。</span></span></strong></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;它是最好的过滤器——帮你重新校准：这家公司到底是在讲性感的宏大故事，还是在踏实地做一门生意？</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">2.《Good to Great》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028013\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.5120967741935485\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"992\" data-width=\"992\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=b1f33a9b&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmd3XAcqricm6tSUp0AdQJnovU40jQmfezRjRqibSkYSqZtktRy0bvWVlMQ%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">中文名：《从优秀到卓越》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Jim Collins（吉姆·柯林斯）</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，美国管理学者和咨询顾问，长期研究企业可持续增长和组织韧性，《基业长青》《从优秀到卓越》等畅销书作者，全球销量逾千万册。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Jesse Zhang，</span><a class=\"normal_text_link\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\" href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==&amp;mid=2247510191&amp;idx=1&amp;sn=b9193ff9d3d892b1a0c4ac1e237f6c70&amp;scene=21#wechat_redirect\" textvalue=\"Decagon\" data-itemshowtype=\"0\" linktype=\"text\" data-linktype=\"2\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Decagon&nbsp;</span></a><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">如果说沃尔顿解决的是「怎么把生意做大」，吉姆·柯林斯解决的是：为什么大多数公司只停留在「不错」，过不了「伟大」那条线？</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">书中提到的「五级领导力」「刺猬理念」「飞轮效应」，本质上是 战略 + 组织 + 时间 的复利组合拳。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;它逼你面对残酷现实——我现在做的是一门好生意，还是一个能成为「伟大公司」的生意？</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;这是判断「这家公司有没有机会穿越周期」的标尺工具书。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h3 style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 24px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">二、产品怎么变成生意：定价、创新与颠覆</span></span></h3>\n   <p></p>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">3.《Crossing the Chasm》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028011\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.5075376884422111\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"995\" data-width=\"995\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=0b1c2d8e&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdpHW8DOicmO08eNSmO8WH1f4ZsJfJ56dIZlbOtUib8Tgrtgpq78K7O5iag%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">中文名</span><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">《跨越鸿沟》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Geoffrey A. Moore</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，科技营销顾问、作家，「鸿沟理论」提出者，The Chasm Group 创始人，长期为高科技公司提供市场进入和定位战略咨询。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Jesse Zhang，Decagon 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这是所有 ToB、开发者工具、深科技创业者的市场圣经。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">它回答了那个经典死法：为什么很多技术极好的产品，最后只活在了一小撮「极客用户」的自嗨里？</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">核心在于如何选择你的「滩头堡市场」，从而跨过早期采用者与主流市场之间那条深不见底的鸿沟。对于「技术很强，但不知道怎么卖」的团队，这本书是救命药。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;如果你正在做 infra、底层工具、API 平台，这本书基本等于「如何从 100 个理想用户走到 1 万个付费客户」的作战手册。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;对投资人，它提供了一套识别「技术不错但永远过不了鸿沟」项目的雷达。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">4.《Monetizing Innovation》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028006\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.5090543259557343\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"994\" data-width=\"994\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=83077a1f&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdibr73suiaY7wp9nYNrFNa9nQ2aChp77TSPpX3gEjiaibTsL0j4nrkfDicmw%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">中文名：《创新变现：以价格为核心的产品设计策略》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Madhavan Ramanujam</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，全球知名定价与货币化专家，长期担任 Simon-Kucher &amp; Partners 合伙人和董事会成员，为上百家科技与互联网公司设计定价与产品策略。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Georg Tacke</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，Simon-Kucher 前 CEO、定价与销售转型专家，拥有 30+ 年咨询经验，被视为全球顶级定价顾问之一，是本书共同作者。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人： Ali Ghodsi，</span><a class=\"normal_text_link\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"\" href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzA3MDU4ODkyNg==&amp;mid=2247506298&amp;idx=1&amp;sn=8879c2b8a2d4677b1f7c101c8bccbeea&amp;scene=21#wechat_redirect\" textvalue=\"Databricks\" data-itemshowtype=\"0\" linktype=\"text\" data-linktype=\"2\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Databricks</span></a><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;联合创始人/CEO</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Databricks 的 CEO 直言这是他心目中的「终极定价书」。它解决了一个被严重低估的问题：</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">很多公司不是死在「没有价值」，而是死在「不会把价值变成收入」。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">书中的原则简单而反直觉：</span></span></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li>\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">不要做完产品再想怎么收费，而是从「谁愿意花多少钱解决什么问题」倒推产品形态。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">对 SaaS、API 平台、AI 工具、订阅制产品来说，这本就是你的 Pricing Playbook。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;本书最重要的一点是：</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">先定价，再做产品</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">——从愿意付费的客户与价格倒推出 roadmap，而不是做完再想怎么收钱。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;这本书帮你判断一个团队是否真正「懂盈利模式」，而不仅是会讲 GMV / 用户数。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">5.《Competing Against Luck》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028004\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.5105740181268883\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"993\" data-width=\"993\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=3ace3e6e&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdOokSLqozkxrZ8CwR2EhNHRogFjQVNI5vq4xZmsCxbNwdPYoNtZTTow%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">中文名：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">《与运气竞争》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Clayton M. Christensen（克莱顿·克里斯坦森）</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，哈佛商学院教授，「颠覆式创新」理论提出者，《创新者的窘境》《创新者的解答》作者，Innosight 咨询公司联合创始人。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Taddy Hall</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，Lippincott 高级合伙人，Jobs-to-be-done 理论实践者，长期为全球企业做创新与增长战略咨询。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Karen Dillon</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，前《哈佛商业评论》主编，与 Christensen 合著多本畅销管理书，现在仍在 HBR 与 Christensen Institute 任职。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">David S. Duncan</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，Innosight 高级合伙人，专注于客户洞察与创新体系建设，是 Jobs-to-be-done 理论的主要实践者之一。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Ali Ghodsi，Databricks 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">本书核心观点振聋发聩：</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">用户不是在「购买一个产品」，而是在「雇佣一个产品帮自己完成某个任务」（Job To Be Done）。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">如果你不知道用户真正要完成的任务是什么，你所有的 A/B Test 可能都在「优化错误的方向」。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;用 JTBD 重写你的 PRD——用户到底在「雇佣」我们做什么？还有哪些场景是他们「应该雇佣我们却没想到」的？</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;帮你迅速从一堆功能堆砌和 Buzzword 里，抽出那条最核心的「被雇佣链条」，判断 PMF 的真伪。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">6.《The Innovator’s Solution》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028007\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.4792899408284024\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"1014\" data-width=\"1014\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=51ceb267&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmd0aMvLVlGSKOyLok0lB28VfZKQQOMF7GCT5KOBicgXkK5XqpEIK9jicibA%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">中文名：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">《创新者的解答》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Clayton M. Christensen</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">：同上（略）。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Michael E. Raynor</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，管理顾问与作家，长期在德勤（Deloitte）等机构从事战略与创新研究，与 Christensen 合著多本关于增长与颠覆的著作。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Jesse Zhang，Decagon 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这本书可以理解为《创新者的窘境》的「操作手册」，告诉你在大公司/平台型公司里，如何设计新业务，避免被母体 KPI 和资源扼杀。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">它特别适合两类人：做平台型公司的创始人，以及在大厂里做「内部创业」的高管。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">它能帮你系统性地判断：眼前的这个新业务，是真的在颠覆，还是只是在老路上换了个新包装？</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;对已经有一定规模的创业公司、正在做多业务线扩张的团队，这是少见的「组织层面」创新指南。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;书里的框架有助于判断：一家大公司说要做新业务，到底是真的有结构性机会，还是在「创新作秀」。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h3 style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 24px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">三、组织与自我管理：招人与用时</span></span></h3>\n   <p></p>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">7.《Who: The A Method for Hiring》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028008\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.5182186234817814\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"988\" data-width=\"988\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=7e13b017&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdibBXV4BYickcDVLG7nAYTy1icHXADIPtpgX9cxKUB8KQ21LmZLqKXC3gA%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">中文名：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">《聘谁》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Geoff Smart</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，ghSMART 创始人及董事长，全球知名领导力与人才顾问，《Who》《Leadocracy》《Power Score》作者，常年为财富 500 强 CEO、创业者和政府领导人提供人才决策咨询。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Randy Street</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，ghSMART 高级合伙人，《Who》的共同作者，被称为「A Method」的主要布道者之一。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Ali Ghodsi，Databricks 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Databricks 的招聘体系正是建立在这本书之上。它强调的不是「如何面试」，而是一整套</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">工程化的招聘流程</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">：</span></span></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">写清楚岗位的 Scorecard（真正要交付的结果，而不是JD）；</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">广撒网找候选人；</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">用结构化面试验证「这人能不能交付那个结果」；</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">严谨的背景调查。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li>\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">对于早期公司，每一次招聘本质上都是一次「股权配置」。招错一个人，不只是多了一个坑位，而是把公司整条发展的时间线拉偏。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li>\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;这套方法可以直接用来问创始团队：「你们现在的招聘流程有多接近这套 A Method？」</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">8.《The Effective Executive》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028009\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.523611111111111\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"720\" data-width=\"720\" data-height=\"1097\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=f9df87b2&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdhibibD6tnxUBzibblw8tyicpAeibZl5PpK4exh7y7icCQqialB8RQ4olgwI5A%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">中文名：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">《卓有成效的管理者》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Peter F. Drucker（彼得·德鲁克）</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，被称为「现代管理学之父」，奥地利裔美国学者，其著作奠定了现代企业管理理论的基础，提出「目标管理（MBO）」等概念，对 20 世纪企业实践影响极深。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Ali Ghodsi，Databricks 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">德鲁克这本书，专门解决 CEO 的隐形焦虑：</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">「当所有人都来找你要时间的时候，你自己的时间还属于你吗？」</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这是所有「从工程师/产品经理转成管理者」的人都应该读的时间与精力管理书：它讨论的是「如何把有限时间用在真正重要的少数事情上」。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></strong></p>\n     <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 创始人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;创业越往后，你真正的工作不是「亲自解决问题」，而是</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">创造一个可以持续解决问题的系统</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n      <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n       <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">To 投资人：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;这是判断创始人是否成长为真正的 Management 的核心标尺。</span></span></p>\n      </li>\n     </ul>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h3 style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 24px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">四、心态与周期：市场风险与内心锚点</span></span></h3>\n   <p></p>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">9.《The Misbehavior of Markets》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028010\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.5416238437821173\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"973\" data-width=\"973\" data-height=\"1500\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=47f4ec92&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdpbiakaiahSMibpbb0BRCdnG57EaIcxRibNvz2qkibp9Gia4nAgAEpYHITM5Q%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">中文名：</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">《市场的非理性行为》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Benoit B. Mandelbrot（伯努瓦·曼德博罗）</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，波兰裔法裔/美籍数学家，「分形几何之父」，长期在 IBM 研究院和耶鲁大学任职，提出曼德博集合，对物理、金融、信息等多个领域影响深远。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Richard L. Hudson</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，财经记者，曾任《华尔街日报》欧洲版总编辑，是本书合作作者，用通俗语言把 Mandelbrot 的数学思想翻译成金融从业者能理解的叙事。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Tarek Mansour，Kalshi 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">曼德博罗用分形几何的视角告诉金融界：真实世界的价格波动，远比教科书假设的「温和正态分布」要疯狂。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这意味着：</span></span></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">估值不会「平滑上升」，周期是剧烈而残酷的；</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">黑天鹅出现的频率，比你想象得高得多；</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">用「过于平滑」的模型来预测未来，是一种危险的自我安慰。</span></span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">对于习惯看漂亮 Excel 曲线的 VC 和创始人，这是一盆清醒的冷水。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></p>\n     <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">对创始人和投资人，这本书最直接的提醒是：</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">黑天鹅不是小概率，极端行情远比你 Excel 里的模型更频繁。</span></span></strong></p>\n     <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">如果你在做金融科技 / 交易基础设施 / 风控产品，本书提供了一套更贴近真实世界的数据直觉。</span></span></p>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h4><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">10.《Man’s Search for Meaning》</span></span></h4>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p nodeleaf=\"\"><img data-imgfileid=\"100028012\" class=\"rich_pages wxw-img\" data-ratio=\"1.6194331983805668\" data-type=\"png\" data-w=\"741\" data-width=\"741\" data-height=\"1200\" src=\"https://wechat2rss.bestblogs.dev/img-proxy/?k=557ddb48&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fmmbiz.qpic.cn%2Fmmbiz_png%2FCHwGFH7ibtQaicibCJrzbBxxia3RC5yZvrmdFKDutC5orGT3VHdOwiczMvRD07ewIF6tfTtQibRXY8R9Nl0U0RvaDycw%2F640%3Fwx_fmt%3Dpng%26from%3Dappmsg\"></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;font-weight: bold;\">中文名：《活出生命的意义》</span></span></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">作者简介：</span></span></strong></p>\n    <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Viktor E. Frankl（维克多·弗兰克尔）</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">，奥地利神经科医生、精神科医生、哲学家，纳粹集中营幸存者，「意义疗法」创立者，被称为「维也纳心理治疗第三学派」。其著作《活出生命的意义》被评为美国最具影响力的图书之一。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">推荐人：Jesse Zhang，Decagon 联合创始人兼首席执行官</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">Jesse 附了一句话：当你读过集中营的故事，再看创业的苦，其实都还好。</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">这本书一半是集中营的亲历，一半是「意义疗法」的理论。</span></span></p>\n    <blockquote>\n     <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">💡 必读理由</span></span></p>\n     <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">创业本质是「高不确定性 + 高压 + 长周期」。</span></span></p>\n     <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">如果你只用「短期结果」来丈量一切，很难避免情绪耗竭。在我们接触的顶级创始人中，真正能走得远的人，很少只靠「野心」撑着，他们多少都找到了某种更深的意义坐标。</span></span></p>\n    </blockquote>\n   </div>\n   <p data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"></p>\n   <h3 style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\"><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 24px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">全文总结：如果今天只能读 3 本</span></span></h3>\n   <p></p>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">如果你现在事务爆炸、时间极度有限，建议按此顺序「极简启动」：</span></span></p>\n    <ul class=\"list-paddingleft-1\">\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">想搞清楚什么叫「做生意」</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;读&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">《Sam Walton: Made in America》</span></span></strong></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">想搞清楚产品为什么有人买</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;读&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">《Monetizing Innovation》</span></span></strong></p>\n     </li>\n     <li style=\"text-align:left;\">\n      <p><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">想搞清楚自己怎么活下去</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;读&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">《The Effective Executive》</span></span></strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">&nbsp;或&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">《Man’s Search for Meaning》</span></span></strong></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <h3><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 18px;color: rgb(255, 169, 0);font-weight: bold;\">互动与福利</span></span></h3>\n   </div>\n   <div data-mid=\"\" mpa-from-tpl=\"t\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;outline: 0px;text-align: left;\">\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">真正重要的不是你书架上多了几本「VC 推荐」，而是这本书帮你做成了哪一个具体决策？过去三年，对你创业/投资影响最大的一本书是什么？</span></span></p>\n    <p><span leaf=\"\"><span textstyle=\"\" style=\"font-size: 15px;\">欢迎在评论区分享书名+理由。我们会精选留言，并优先邀请你加入 SVTR 的读书 &amp; 创投交流群，一起聊聊这25本书和创业投资。</span></span></p>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "文章精选 a16z 创始人和合伙人推荐的 25 本书中的 10 本，并按商业本质、产品变现、组织管理和心力建设四个维度，为创始人与投资人提供认知升级的必读清单。",
